  "texts": [
    "Combining the facts that G ′ j ⊩ (□ ▷ ⊥ ∧ □ ◁ ⊥) → χ, G ′ k ⊮ (□ ▷ ⊥ ∧ □ ◁ ⊥) → χ, and F ⊩ (□ ▷ ⊥ ∧ □ ◁ ⊥) → χ, it follows by Proposi- tion 5.57 that F G ′ j ⊩ (□ ▷ ⊥ ∧ □ ◁ ⊥) → χ but F G ′ k ⊮ (□ ▷ ⊥ ∧ □ ◁ ⊥) → χ.",
    "Thus, we have established (ii).Now we prove the claim about Kripke-frame inconsistent logics.",
    "For each j ∈ J, let (F G ′ j) ′ be obtained from F G ′ j by making the accessibility relation for i the universal relation in (F G ′ j) ′ and changing nothing else.",
    "First, it is easy to check that (F G ′ j) ′ is still a full possibility frame.",
    "Second, from the fact that (Split) is valid over F G ′ j, it is easy to check that (Split) is valid over (F G ′ j) ′."
